HB 982 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Thompson
Designates a portion of La. Hwy. 133 North in the Village of Oak Ridge, between south of
Fluker Lane and the Village of Oak Ridge corporate limits, as the "Erle McKoin 'Niney'
Barham Memorial Highway".
Designates a portion of La. Hwy. 133 South in the Village of Oak Ridge, between north of
Buck Shepard Road and the Village of Oak Ridge corporate limits, as the "Joseph Sidney
Carter Memorial Highway".
Designates a portion of La. Hwy. 134 West in the Village of Oak Ridge, between east of
Lake Erwin Road and the Village of Oak Ridge corporate limits, as the "Abner Wimberly
Memorial Highway".
Designates a portion of La. Hwy. 134 East in the Village of Oak Ridge, between west of
Pipes Lane and the Village of Oak Ridge corporate limits, as the "James Wallace McLendon
Memorial Highway".
Directs the Dept. of Transportation and Development (DOTD) to erect and maintain
appropriate signage reflecting the hwy. designations provided local or private monies are
received by the DOTD equal to its actual costs for material, fabrication, mounting posts, and
installation of the signage, not to exceed the sum of $750 per sign.
